Spain is located in southwest Europe along the Mediterranean sea. Known for it's rich history and great weather, it is an amazing place to visit. Barcelona is known as one of the most beautiful cities in the world and has unique architecture and a unique city layout. Spain is full of inspiring beauty and stanning landscapes, combining both natural wonder in it's diverse landscape and also bustling, beautiful cities rich with culture.

Population: 46,794,717

Capital City: Madrid

Currency Exchange Rate: 1 USD equals 1 Euro

Places to Visit: Barcelona is known as one of the most beautiful cities in the world and has some of the most unique layouts in the world as well. There is no shortage of things to do in Spain and cities to visit from Barcelona, to the capital Madrid, to Sevilla and many more. The landscapes are just as beautiful as the city and the rich history provides limitless possibilities for you to explore.

For more in-depth information on where to visit and why see: https://theculturetrip.com/europe/spain/articles/the-15-best-destinations-to-visit-in-spain-in-2018/

Transportation Info: Being a part of the EU, there are many different transportation options from buses to trains.